<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 11 at 9:42AM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...Increased fire danger for much of the western Piedmont of
central North Carolina from noon until 6 pm today...
The combination of frequent wind gusts to 20 to 30 mph, low
relative humidity values near 20 percent, and dry fuels and tree
litter will lead to an increased fire danger this afternoon over
western portions of central North Carolina.
Residents are urged to exercise caution handling any potential
ignition source. Be sure to properly discard all smoking
materials. Any dry grasses and tree litter that ignite will have
the potential to spread quickly.</description>
